Fourth-place Monaco missed the chance to close the gap in the French title race after drawing 0-0 at home to Montpellier on Tuesday .
A win would have moved Monaco level on points with third-place Marseille .
The visitors missed a penalty early in the second half when Paraguay striker Lucas Barrios fired a penalty to the crossbar .
Monaco is two points behind Marseille , six behind Lyon and seven behind Paris Saint-Germain .